# Architecture Rules

## Manifest V3
- Service worker only (never Manifest V2 background page)
- `host_permissions`: `https://www.youtube.com/*`, `https://studio.youtube.com/*` only
- Prefer static `content_scripts` over `chrome.scripting.executeScript` (cleaner Chrome Web Store review)
- Background: `"type": "module"`
- Minimal permissions: `storage`, `activeTab`, `sidePanel`, `alarms`

## YouTube SPA Navigation (CRITICAL)
YouTube is a SPA тАФ `DOMContentLoaded` fires only once.
- Watch URL changes via `MutationObserver` on `document.body` comparing `location.href`
- Also listen for custom `yt-navigate-finish` on `document` when available
- Debounce `init()` by 1000тАУ1500ms after URL change (DOM hydration delay)
- Use incrementing `initId` to cancel stale async work (race condition guard)
- Disconnect observer on `pagehide`
- Re-inject UI on every navigation, not only first load

## YouTube Data Extraction (`youtube-scraper.js`)
Always use `waitForElement(selector, timeoutMs)` before reading dynamic nodes.

| Field | Primary selector | Fallbacks |
|-------|------------------|-----------|
| videoId | `new URLSearchParams(location.search).get('v')` | `/[?&]v=([^&]+)/` on `location.href` |
| title | `ytd-watch-metadata #title yt-formatted-string` | `h1.ytd-watch-metadata yt-formatted-string`, `h1.title yt-formatted-string`, `document.title.replace(' - YouTube','')` |
| channel | `#owner #channel-name a` | `ytd-channel-name a`, `ytInitialPlayerResponse.videoDetails.author` |
| description | `#description-inline-expander #snippet-text` | `#description-text` |
| thumbnail | `https://img.youtube.com/vi/{videoId}/maxresdefault.jpg` | `hqdefault.jpg`, `mqdefault.jpg` |

Transcript extraction priority:
1. Injected page script reads `window.ytInitialPlayerResponse?.captions?.playerCaptionsTracklistRenderer?.captionTracks`
2. Parse `captionTracks` JSON from inline `<script>` HTML
3. Fetch caption XML/JSON from `baseUrl + '&fmt=json3'` or `&fmt=vtt`
4. Click "Show transcript" and scrape `.ytd-transcript-segment-renderer` or `.segment-timestamp` + `.segment-text`

`ytInitialPlayerResponse` lives in page MAIN world тАФ use `chrome.scripting.executeScript({ world: 'MAIN', func })` from service worker OR inject a `<script>` tag that `postMessage`s results back. Content script isolated world cannot read it directly.

Never assume selectors are stable тАФ wrap every read in try/catch with fallbacks.

## Thumbnail Fetch (CORS)
Fetch thumbnails from service worker or background, not content script canvas:
```javascript
const res = await fetch(thumbnailUrl);
const blob = await res.blob();
const base64 = await blobToBase64(blob); // FileReader in service worker
```

## Messaging (`lib/messaging.js`)
```javascript
export async function sendMessage(type, data = {}) {
  try {
    const res = await chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ type, ...data });
    if (res?.error) return { success: false, message: res.error };
    return res ?? {};
  } catch (err) {
    return { success: false, message: err.message };
  }
}
```

Message types: `EXTRACT_VIDEO_DATA`, `ANALYZE_THUMBNAIL`, `GENERATE_SEO`, `GENERATE_HOOKS`, `SUMMARIZE_TRANSCRIPT`

## AI Integration

### Provider priority
1. Backend proxy (`/api/analyze-thumbnail`, `/api/generate-seo`)
2. Direct BYOK from service worker
3. Demo mode тАФ show template output, never throw to UI

### Gemini (default)
- Model: `gemini-2.5-flash` for vision + JSON (NOT `gemini-2.5-flash-image` тАФ no JSON mode)
- Always set both `responseMimeType: "application/json"` AND `responseSchema`
- Resize thumbnails to max 1280px width before base64
- Temperature: 0.3 analysis, 0.7 creative titles

```javascript
generationConfig: {
  responseMimeType: 'application/json',
  responseSchema: { type: 'object', properties: { /* ... */ }, required: ['ctr_score'] },
  temperature: 0.3
}
```

### OpenAI vision fallback
- Model: `gpt-4o` (not 4o-mini for vision quality)
- Use `detail: 'low'` for simple thumbnail scoring (lower token cost)
- `response_format: { type: 'json_object' }`

