### Security (NEVER violate)
- NEVER store API keys in content scripts or page DOM
- NEVER commit API keys
- Keys only in `chrome.storage.local`, read from service worker/backend
- Sanitize AI output before DOM injection (`textContent` or DOMPurify)
- YouTube Data API calls only from backend (key protection)

# UI/UX
- Primary UI: Side Panel
- Loading skeleton during AI calls (5тАУ15s)
- CTR badge: red <5, yellow 5тАУ7, green >7
- Copy buttons for title/description
- Friendly error messages (Hindi + English), never raw API errors
- Options: API key, provider (Gemini/OpenAI), language (hi/en)

# Code Quality
- ES modules, explicit imports
- try/catch on all async with user-friendly fallback
- No globals тАФ module scope only
- Functions <50 lines; extract helpers when longer
- JSDoc on exports
- camelCase functions, UPPER_SNAKE constants
- Debug logging behind `DEBUG` flag only

# What NOT to Do
- No Manifest V2, jQuery, React/Vue/webpack (unless requested)
- No AI calls from content scripts
- No `<all_urls>` host_permissions
- No blocking YouTube rendering
- No CTR-only optimization тАФ always mention Quality CTR (CTR + retention alignment)
- No refactor of unrelated files per task
- Do not use `gemini-2.5-flash-image` for JSON structured output

